	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philad.</placeName> <date>February 13&#47;56</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><sic>Inclosed</sic> please find the article to be<lb/> inserted in your next <sic>occident</sic>&#44; I find it all right&#44; with the<lb/> exception of the circumstance as it <sic>happend</sic>&#44; which you<lb/> will find below&#44; so if you think proper or <sic>necessairy</sic> please attend.<lb/>  If you wish to make any other alteration&#44; or additions<lb/> I am satisfied&#44; &#38; leave it to your good <sic>judment</sic>&#44; but<lb/> inserted I will have the affair.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain yours with respect</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">J H Carbstadter</persName></p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Circumstance</hi></p>
				<p>The gentlemen whom I send <del>dit</del> <sic>calld</sic> twice at the<lb/> ministers house&#44; but <sic>dit</sic> not find him at home&#44; therefore when<lb/> the Minyan were assembled&#44; some one ask for the minister&#44; the<lb/> gentlemen stated as above&#44; consequently we <sic>comenced</sic>&#44; some one<lb/> &#40;not a minister&#41; offered to read the service.  Only after the minister<lb/> arrived we <sic>ascertaind</sic> that some one else had notified him of it&#44;<lb/> which we assure the public <sic>dit</sic> not remember any more&#44; of having<lb/> a day previous &#40;on the day when we received the sad tidings&#41; requested some<lb/> one else to notify the minister.  The public will judge in what<lb/> situation we were in after receiving <add>&#63;</add> news&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will please write the above correct&#44; if you<lb/> <sic>dont</sic> find it so&#44; &#38; change it as you think proper.<lb/>  If you please <add>&#63;</add> <persName role="author">J. H.</persName> as I <sic>dont</sic> wish to make myself<lb/> to <sic>conspictious</sic> before the public&#44; but if you think it <sic>nessesaire</sic> to have the<lb/> name in full you may do it</p>
		</body>
